# --- Prettier scope policy (DevFlows) ---
# The devflows generator (`devflows sync` / `devflows test-generate`) is the sole
# formatting authority for GitHub Actions workflow YAML. Prettier must never
# reformat generator-owned files, or it would fight `devflows sync --check`:
#   * generated public + scenario workflows and their support files under
#     .github/workflows/** (the generator emits its own YAML style, e.g. quoted
#     'on': keys, which prettier would rewrite)
#   * catalog sources under workflows/** (workflow.yaml is re-emitted by the
#     generator; devflow.yaml metadata is authored to match those outputs)
# Hand-written operational workflows also live under .github/workflows/ and are
# linted by actionlint + zizmor + yamllint, so workflow YAML formatting as a whole
# stays out of prettier's scope. Prettier still owns docs (*.md) and standalone
# config (*.json, non-workflow *.yml/*.yaml such as .prettierrc.yaml and the
# release-please config).

# Generator-owned / actionlint-owned GitHub Actions workflows (see policy above)
.github/workflows/
workflows/

# Environments, caches, and local agent scratch directories
.pixi/
.codex/
.claude/
.devcontainer/

# Generated documentation output
docs/_build/
docs/reference/

# Generated lock files (owned by their tooling, not prettier)
pixi.lock
